Sequencing Center: Institute for Biodiversity and Ecosystem dynamics, Faculty of Science, University of Amsterdam
Comments: In this study we examined the vertical distribution of genes and transcripts originating from dissimilatory sulfur-cycling prokaryotes in the water and surface sediments of Cock soda lake, a relatively large hypersaline soda lake in the Kulunda Steppe (South-Western Siberia, Russian Federation).
